    "description": "An ancient place, cited: BAtlas 18 E2 Cambete",
    "details": "<p>The Barrington Atlas Directory notes: Kembs? SWI. The toponym \"Cambete\" appears twice on the Peutinger map, once on segment 2A3 and again on 2A4. Talbert notes that the most likely explanation for this occurrence is that the copyist has duplicated a route and its associated toponyms in error.</p>",
